{
  "texts": [
    "Surprisingly, GPT3.5, the cheaper alternative, can produce exercises comparable in quality to GPT4o.",
    "This means that GPT3.5 can be used to power BugSpotter as a scalable solution in terms of cost, without compromising quality.",
    "RQ2: Expert-assessed Difficulty and Student Performance on Debugging ExercisesFor each problem, we analyze the 5 pre-selected exercises generated by LLMs as described in Section 4.",
    "Difficulty is often a key factor in deciding whether exercises should be assigned to students [19], so it is important for BugSpotter to produce a range of difficulties from which students can choose.",
    "We study this diversity from both the perspective of an expert and empirically based on student performance."
  ]
}